**Code Explanation:**

The code conducts an ablation study by comparing two variants of the Graph Neural Network (GNN) emulator: a "Physics-Informed" model (which includes the analytical gravitational force with softening as an input feature) and a "Learned-Only" model (which relies solely on raw positions and velocities). First, it trains the Learned-Only model using the same training protocol and dataset splits established in previous steps. It checks for the existence of the pre-trained Physics-Informed model (from Step 3) to avoid redundant computation. Next, both models are evaluated on the held-out test set (10 simulations, 10 snapshots each) to compute the Mean Squared Error (MSE) of the predicted accelerations against the ground-truth leapfrog accelerations. The MSE has units of (L/T^2)^2. Finally, the script prints the numerical MSE values for both models and generates a side-by-side bar chart to visually quantify the impact of the physical prior on the network's ability to learn the underlying dynamics.

**Modifications:**

Added units (L/T^2)^2 to the y-axis label. Changed the y-axis to a logarithmic scale (plt.yscale('log')) to make both bars clearly visible despite the large difference in magnitude. Formatted the text labels on top of the bars to display only 3 decimal places for better readability. Adjusted the text placement to work well with the logarithmic scale.

